    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera S (997.1) in concours-level condition. This specimen features the 3.8L M97 flat-six, delivering 355 hp through a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The mechanical integrity is superlative, featuring a documented IMS solution and a recently replaced clutch assembly. Performance is optimized via Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and a factory-spec limited-slip differential, ensuring razor-sharp turn-in. A recent borescope inspection confirms zero cylinder scoring, and the DME report shows no over-revs in ranges 3-6. The exterior retains its mirror-like finish, while the cabin shows zero bolster wear. Equipped with original four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors, this 997 offers a pure, analog driving experience with comprehensive service provenance.",
